        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 7:22PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 721 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Indian Creek, or near Brookesmith, moving southeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Brookesmith, Regency, Spring Creek, Locker, and Indian Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for
west central Texas.</instruction>
